'''San Pietro''' (Church of St Peter) is a [[Byzantine architecture|Byzantine]] style, [[Roman Catholic]] church located in the town of [[Frascineto]], [[Province of Cosenza]], region of [[Calabria]], Italy.

==History==
The church was built in the 10th-century, and was property of [[Basilian monks|Basilian Order]] monks until the 18th century. The nave, with two aisles, is oriented towards the west and has an apse, cupola and presbytery that are typically Byzantine. The church is presently deconsecrated. The dome is layers and roofed in tiles.<ref>[http://www.comune.frascineto.cs.it/Home/Guidaalpaese/tabid/25383/Default.aspx?IDDettaglio=10075 Comune di Frascineto], tourism entry.</ref>

